In [651]:
# Deriving "days since the show started"
from datetime import date

d0 = date(2018, 1, 1)
delta = []
for d in df.dteday:
    delta.append(d.date() - d0)
df['day']= delta

In [653]:
#Converting categorical season variables 
varlist = ['season']

def seasonFunc(x):
    return x.map({1:'spring', 2:'summer', 3:'fall', 4:'winter'})

season_group = df[varlist]
season_group = season_group.apply(seasonFunc)

df['season'] = season_group
In [655]:
#Converting categorical weathersit variables 
varlist = ['weathersit']

def weathersitFunc(x):
    return x.map({1:'Good_weathr', 2:'Avg_weathr', 3:'Bad_weathr', 4:'VeryBad_weathr'})

weather_group = df[varlist]
weather_group = weather_group.apply(weathersitFunc)

df['weathersit'] = weather_group
In [654]:
#Converting categorical  weekday variables 
varlist = ['weekday']

def weekdayFunc(x):
    return x.map({0:'Sunday', 1:'Monday', 2:'Tuesday', 3:'Wednesday',4:'Thrusday', 5:'Friday', 6:'Saturday'})

weekday_group = df[varlist]
weekday_group = weekday_group.apply(weekdayFunc)

df['weekday'] = weekday_group
In [656]:
#Converting categorical mnth variables 
varlist = ['mnth']

def mthFunc(x):
    return x.map({1:'January', 2:'February', 3:'March',4:'April', 5:'May', 6:'June',7:'July', 8:'Aug', 9:'Sept',10:'Oct', 11:'Nov', 12:'Dec'})

mnth_group = df[varlist]
mnth_group = mnth_group.apply(mthFunc)

df['mnth'] = mnth_group

Final Remarks on Variables¶

  • Hypthosesis Testing [Null Hypothesis - Bx=0 || Alternate Kypothesis - Bx !=0 ]

    • Coefficient values in final model 6th iteration is as follows :
      • const 0.0442
      • yr 0.2332
      • temp 0.5527
      • windspeed -0.1552
      • season_summer 0.0894
      • season_winter 0.1281
      • mnth_Sept 0.0978
      • weathersit_Bad_weathr -0.2019
      • weathersit_Good_weathr 0.0767
    • As we see the beta coefficients have non zero value, Hence we can reject the null kypothesis which means Model is significant .
    • ALso , please note F statistic is [ F-statistic: 296.5] , with a p -value of approximate 0 which means model is signifant .

  • Top Three Predictor variables are :

    • temp [0.5527] . An increase of temp will increase the bike request.
    • yr[0.2332] . AN increase in years will increase the bike request . This might be due to increase in popularity .
